WEBVTT

00:04.178 --> 00:06.876
<i>- Previously
on "New Amsterdam"...</i>

00:06.919 --> 00:08.704
- I love you.

00:08.747 --> 00:11.620
<i>[soft piano music]</i>

00:11.663 --> 00:14.492
<i>- They keep hammering on
at you to open up,</i>

00:14.536 --> 00:17.669
<i>but that has to go both ways.</i>

00:17.713 --> 00:19.193
<i>- And even though my body
is telling me</i>

00:19.236 --> 00:22.631
to just let go and jump,
I can't.

00:22.674 --> 00:24.024
Not even for you.

00:24.067 --> 00:26.200
<i>- I gave Chance everything.</i>

00:26.243 --> 00:27.940
<i>I just wanted him
to get better.</i>

00:27.984 --> 00:30.769
<i>But it was never enough.</i>

00:30.813 --> 00:32.467
- If you don't
have to fight for it,

00:32.509 --> 00:34.556
it's 'cause it's not worth it.

00:37.385 --> 00:40.518
<i>[melancholy piano music]</i>

00:40.562 --> 00:46.176
<i>♪</i>

00:46.220 --> 00:47.786
<i>- Leave a message
after the tone.</i>

00:47.830 --> 00:49.136
<i>[phone beeps]</i>

00:49.179 --> 00:50.789
<i>- Hey.</i>

00:50.833 --> 00:53.270
<i>It's, uh, me.</i>

00:53.314 --> 00:57.231
<i>I--I miss you.</i>

00:57.274 --> 00:59.146
<i>I can't get you
out of my head.</i>

00:59.189 --> 01:02.801
<i>It's, uh,
it's very distracting.</i>

01:02.845 --> 01:04.063
<i>Um...</i>

01:06.066 --> 01:11.288
<i>We said things to each other
that were just the beginning.</i>

01:11.332 --> 01:16.293
<i>And we never quite, um--</i>

01:16.337 --> 01:18.034
<i>anyway, now you're gone,</i>

01:18.078 --> 01:22.125
<i>and it just feels like
it's been forever.</i>

01:22.169 --> 01:26.086
<i>And I really need...
[sighs]</i>

01:26.129 --> 01:27.652
<i>I need to see you.</i>

01:29.350 --> 01:32.092
<i>I need to talk to you.</i>

01:32.135 --> 01:35.965
<i>I need to be with you</i>

01:36.008 --> 01:40.100
<i>in all of the ways
that I've been dreaming of.</i>

01:40.143 --> 01:42.276
[machine whirring]

01:42.319 --> 01:44.713
<i>- And we're done.</i>

01:44.756 --> 01:46.236
- All right. Easy enough.

01:46.280 --> 01:47.585
- Everything looks good,
Dr. Goodwin.

01:47.629 --> 01:48.847
- Fantastic.

01:48.891 --> 01:51.285
Thank you so much.
- See you in six months.

01:52.851 --> 01:55.811
- [humming]

02:00.598 --> 02:03.732
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

02:03.775 --> 02:05.908
<i>♪</i>

02:05.951 --> 02:07.605
- Is everything okay?

02:07.649 --> 02:09.955
- [chuckles]

02:09.999 --> 02:12.219
Have you seen my wedding ring?

02:12.262 --> 02:13.742
- Sure haven't.

02:20.009 --> 02:22.838
<i>[soft piano music]</i>

02:22.881 --> 02:23.882
<i>♪</i>

02:23.926 --> 02:27.147
<i>- [sighs]
I need to see you.</i>

02:27.190 --> 02:29.410
<i>I need to talk to you.</i>

02:29.453 --> 02:32.891
<i>I need to be with you</i>

02:32.935 --> 02:37.113
<i>in all of the ways
that I've been dreaming of.</i>

02:37.157 --> 02:39.202
- [sighs]
And this one's too tight.

02:39.246 --> 02:41.117
Everything looks terrible
on me.

02:41.161 --> 02:44.773
- Oh, stop that.
You're just nervous.

02:44.816 --> 02:46.296
- Wonder why.
It's only the beginning

02:46.340 --> 02:48.211
of the rest of my whole life.

02:48.255 --> 02:49.604
- [chuckles]

02:51.780 --> 02:54.174
<i>[line trilling]</i>

02:54.217 --> 02:55.479
<i>- Hey. You've reached Max.</i>

02:55.523 --> 02:57.089
<i>I can't take your call,
so leave a message.</i>

02:57.133 --> 02:59.657
<i>[phone beeps]
- Hi. Um.</i>

02:59.701 --> 03:02.747
I very much
enjoyed your message.

03:02.791 --> 03:05.359
My flight's not till tomorrow,
but, um...

03:08.100 --> 03:11.887
I've been doing
some fantasizing of my own.

03:11.930 --> 03:13.758
- Okay.

03:13.802 --> 03:15.282
I'm ready. I think.

03:15.325 --> 03:16.935
<i>[line beeps]
- [sighs]</i>

03:16.979 --> 03:23.899
<i>♪</i>

03:23.942 --> 03:26.771
- You can't be serious.
- Oh, don't sound so surprised.

03:26.815 --> 03:28.425
I was never gonna
stay here forever.

03:28.469 --> 03:30.862
- But today?
But today?

03:30.906 --> 03:33.561
- I'm gonna try and catch
a standby flight.

03:33.604 --> 03:35.867
- But I wanted you to come back
to Cambridge with me.

03:35.911 --> 03:37.956
- I know.

03:38.000 --> 03:40.350
I've had a wonderful time.

03:40.394 --> 03:42.047
But you're all set up
in the halls.

03:42.091 --> 03:43.919
You have an amazing dress.

03:46.051 --> 03:50.273
And most importantly,
you don't need me anymore.

03:50.317 --> 03:56.932
<i>♪</i>

03:57.933 --> 03:59.761
I'm so proud of you.

04:03.112 --> 04:05.897
- You took me into your home.

04:05.941 --> 04:07.682
You never gave up on me.

04:09.379 --> 04:11.990
I don't know how to thank you.

04:12.034 --> 04:14.384
- You don't need to.

04:14.428 --> 04:16.038
You don't need to.
We're family.

04:22.130 --> 04:25.003
- [speaking Farsi]

04:37.146 --> 04:40.236
- And text me when you're
at the airport, okay?

04:40.280 --> 04:41.411
- I will.

04:41.455 --> 04:44.022
I just have
one more stop to make.

04:49.071 --> 04:55.991
<i>♪</i>

05:22.234 --> 05:23.366
Sorry I'm late, Mum.

05:23.410 --> 05:24.498
- Now that you're here,
we can leave.

05:24.541 --> 05:26.238
I made you some red-red.

05:26.282 --> 05:29.938
No use spending hard-earned
money on beetroot foam.

05:29.981 --> 05:32.157
- [laughs] Well, let me
do this for you, Mum.

05:32.201 --> 05:34.246
It's a meal.

05:34.290 --> 05:35.639
And it's really good
to see you.

05:35.683 --> 05:37.772
- Glad you found time
to fit me in.

05:39.121 --> 05:41.471
- Yeah, uh, Nina got
into King's College

05:41.515 --> 05:43.430
in Cambridge.
It's been a busy week.

05:43.473 --> 05:44.474
I wanted to help her
get set up.

05:44.518 --> 05:46.476
- So, the truth comes out.

05:48.478 --> 05:52.090
- Mum, she is wonderful.

05:52.134 --> 05:54.484
She's smart, she's driven,

05:54.528 --> 05:57.400
and she is family.

05:57.444 --> 05:59.054
And since I'm going back
to New York,

05:59.097 --> 06:01.099
I put you down
as her emergency contact,

06:01.143 --> 06:02.362
and I think that
if you would just meet her--

06:02.405 --> 06:03.798
- Not on your life.
- Mum.

06:03.841 --> 06:05.408
- You say no all the time.

06:05.452 --> 06:07.671
No to London,
no husband, no baby.

06:07.715 --> 06:09.325
Why must I say yes?

06:09.369 --> 06:13.198
But please, daughter, give me
that other woman's grandchild.

06:13.242 --> 06:16.114
- We are blood.

06:16.158 --> 06:17.855
And since Baba
was kept away from me--

06:17.899 --> 06:19.379
- I didn't keep
your father from you.

06:19.422 --> 06:21.816
He cut off ties.
He went home to Tehran

06:21.859 --> 06:23.861
and found his ready-made
Persian wife.

06:23.905 --> 06:25.080
He abandoned us.

06:25.123 --> 06:26.429
- Okay, so now what?

06:26.473 --> 06:29.519
Hmm?
We abandon her?

06:29.563 --> 06:31.739
- You spent the past week

06:31.782 --> 06:34.394
ignoring your own mother
for that other family.

06:34.437 --> 06:36.265
Turns out you're
just like your baba.

06:36.308 --> 06:39.399
[coughing]

06:48.016 --> 06:50.671
- Mum, how long have you
had that cough?

06:50.714 --> 06:52.412
- A few weeks.
[clears throat]

06:52.455 --> 06:54.152
Or more.

06:54.196 --> 06:55.719
You'd know if you ever rang.

06:55.763 --> 06:57.939
- Come on.
We're gonna go, Mum.

06:57.982 --> 06:59.244
Come on.

06:59.288 --> 07:06.164
<i>♪</i>

07:07.514 --> 07:08.950
[indistinct chatter]

07:08.993 --> 07:10.517
[bottles clanking]

07:10.560 --> 07:13.345
[person shouting indistinctly]

07:13.389 --> 07:14.999
- This is your old clinic.

07:15.043 --> 07:16.740
- Yes.

07:16.784 --> 07:19.003
It's certainly seen
better days.

07:20.657 --> 07:23.051
Excuse me. Hi.

07:25.880 --> 07:28.230
Hi, I was hoping to get my mum
in today for some scans.

07:28.273 --> 07:30.928
She's had a persistent cough,
and today we found some blood.

07:30.972 --> 07:32.843
- We're booked solid,
I'm afraid.

07:32.887 --> 07:34.932
I could maybe get her in
early next week.

07:34.976 --> 07:37.065
- This is why
I never bother with doctors.

07:37.108 --> 07:39.154
[phone buzzing]
- No, Mum, wait, wait.

07:42.113 --> 07:45.029
Uh, sorry. Excuse me.
My name is Dr. Helen Sharpe.

07:45.073 --> 07:46.901
I used to volunteer here
when I was in college.

07:46.944 --> 07:49.120
I started behind the desk,
just like you,

07:49.164 --> 07:50.948
but this clinic
is where I found my passion,

07:50.992 --> 07:54.169
and now I'm pleading with you.

07:54.212 --> 07:56.998
I need to make sure
that my mum gets seen.

08:01.655 --> 08:03.483
- I can move things around.

08:03.526 --> 08:05.528
- Thank you. Thank you.

08:05.572 --> 08:07.574
- No, I don't want
any special treatment.

08:07.617 --> 08:08.879
I don't like my daughter
pulling strings

08:08.923 --> 08:10.141
just so we can jump the queue.

08:10.185 --> 08:12.230
- Mum, we are taking
the opening

08:12.274 --> 08:13.971
whether you like it or not.
End of discussion.

08:14.015 --> 08:15.625
- Right this way.
I'll take you back.

08:15.669 --> 08:17.627
- Thank you.

08:17.671 --> 08:19.411
- No, I don't need you
to come with me.

08:19.455 --> 08:21.501
I can do this all on my own.

08:25.417 --> 08:29.334
<i>♪</i>

08:29.378 --> 08:31.293
- [snoring softly]

08:34.208 --> 08:36.254
- Helen?

08:36.298 --> 08:39.082
As I live and breathe.

08:39.126 --> 08:41.172
- Elinor.

08:41.216 --> 08:43.000
I didn't know
you were still here.

08:43.044 --> 08:44.654
- There's still work to do.
What's your excuse?

08:44.698 --> 08:45.960
No more New York?

08:46.003 --> 08:49.006
- My mum's sick.
She's getting seen.

08:50.878 --> 08:52.880
Can I just ask? Um...

08:52.923 --> 08:56.187
This place--what happened?

08:56.231 --> 08:58.363
- We started hemorrhaging staff
due to Brexit.

08:58.407 --> 09:01.105
And then we lost the funding
we used to get from Cambridge,

09:01.149 --> 09:03.325
and it all started
to fall apart.

09:03.368 --> 09:06.633
Last month, our medical
director packed up and left.

09:06.676 --> 09:09.200
Now we're fighting to hold on.

09:09.244 --> 09:11.028
- This place is too special
to just--

09:11.072 --> 09:13.074
- Dr. Sharpe, can you join me?

09:15.729 --> 09:17.121
- It was good
to see you, Elinor.

09:17.165 --> 09:18.993
- Oh, you too, love.
- Mm-hmm.

09:22.387 --> 09:23.824
Thank you.

09:23.867 --> 09:26.740
<i>[soft dramatic piano music]</i>

09:26.783 --> 09:33.921
<i>♪</i>

09:35.879 --> 09:37.838
I'm right here, Mum.

09:40.275 --> 09:43.060
I'm not going anywhere.

09:43.104 --> 09:46.237
- So I just wanted you
to see what we found today.

09:53.114 --> 09:54.942
- Run blood tests on Bay 26,

09:54.985 --> 09:56.770
and let's send her up
for a stress echo.

09:56.813 --> 09:58.380
- Why hasn't Bay 9
been discharged?

09:58.423 --> 10:01.165
- Because I possibly forgot.
On it.

10:01.209 --> 10:04.212
<i>[indistinct PA announcements]</i>

10:04.255 --> 10:06.214
- Hey, have you, uh,
have you heard from Iggy?

10:06.257 --> 10:08.390
- Uh, no. Not in weeks. You?

10:08.433 --> 10:10.479
- Radio silence.
I've been thinking about him.

10:10.522 --> 10:13.003
But--uh, what's up?

10:13.047 --> 10:14.744
- Nothing. Stupid.
I lost my wedding ring.

10:14.788 --> 10:16.050
- Yikes.
- Yeah.

10:16.093 --> 10:17.399
But it's okay. No big deal.

10:17.442 --> 10:18.356
I mean, it's not like
it's worth

10:18.400 --> 10:19.619
a ton of money or anything.

10:19.662 --> 10:22.447
It's just a little silly ring,
you know?

10:22.491 --> 10:23.884
But it's gotta be in here
somewhere.

10:23.927 --> 10:26.060
Okay, who loses one shoe?

10:26.103 --> 10:27.583
- Well, where did you
take it off?

10:27.627 --> 10:29.759
- I--I don't take it off.

10:29.803 --> 10:31.413
- Not even at night?
- No.

10:31.456 --> 10:33.545
- Well, what about to scrub in?
- No.

10:33.589 --> 10:35.069
- Not even when you were
dating that woman?

10:35.112 --> 10:38.072
- Never. Okay?
I never take it off.

10:38.115 --> 10:40.378
- 26-year-old. Tachy at 148.

10:40.422 --> 10:44.644
100/56, respiratory rate 14
from an abdominal stab wound.

10:44.687 --> 10:47.211
- From Excalibur?
- Cosplay gone horribly wrong.

10:47.255 --> 10:49.561
- Oh, that's a ton of blood
for a wound in that area.

10:49.605 --> 10:51.651
Let's page Reynolds now.
Trauma one.

10:51.694 --> 10:52.913
Gauze.

10:52.956 --> 10:55.742
[machinery beeping]

10:55.785 --> 10:57.047
<i>[tense music]</i>

10:57.091 --> 11:01.138
Gauze. Gauze. Gauze.

11:01.182 --> 11:03.184
Damn it, keep them coming.

11:03.227 --> 11:04.751
The puncture's bad,
but it shouldn't cause

11:04.794 --> 11:06.274
loss of consciousness.

11:06.317 --> 11:08.755
- Dr. Bloom, look at this.

11:08.798 --> 11:10.452
- Negative P waves?

11:10.495 --> 11:13.020
- And negative QRS,
and T waves, plus low voltage?

11:13.063 --> 11:14.195
What the hell?

11:14.238 --> 11:16.458
- Dextrocardia.

11:16.501 --> 11:18.678
- Her heart's on the wrong side
of her chest.

11:20.723 --> 11:23.508
- Boy, do I have
a great case for you.

11:23.552 --> 11:26.424
- Dextrocardia doesn't explain
the excessive bleeding.

11:26.468 --> 11:28.905
- Unless she also has
complete situs inversus.

11:28.949 --> 11:32.039
Not just her heart, but all
of her organs were flipped.

11:32.082 --> 11:34.345
- Then her spleen
is on the right side.

11:34.389 --> 11:36.304
- Which means the dagger
is going right through it.

11:36.347 --> 11:38.262
- But that doesn't
explain the LOC.

11:38.306 --> 11:40.003
- Stop for a head CT
on your way to the OR.

11:40.047 --> 11:41.309
- Good idea.

11:48.359 --> 11:51.406
- Hey, you.
What's going on?

11:52.537 --> 11:54.714
- The residency match list
came out.

11:55.976 --> 11:57.325
I got a spot.

11:57.368 --> 12:01.155
- You did?
Oh, that's amazing.

12:01.198 --> 12:03.331
- [sighs]
I honestly can't believe it.

12:03.374 --> 12:04.811
- Well, don't look
so surprised.

12:04.854 --> 12:06.116
Have you met you?
- Stop.

12:06.160 --> 12:07.770
You know how competitive
these things are.

12:07.814 --> 12:09.337
And it was my very first try.

12:09.380 --> 12:10.860
And I'm
a foreign-trained doctor.

12:10.904 --> 12:12.993
- And you blew them all away.

12:13.036 --> 12:15.082
- Well, not all.

12:15.125 --> 12:16.387
I didn't get a spot here.

12:16.431 --> 12:18.650
But we knew that was
gonna be a long shot.

12:18.694 --> 12:20.348
- Wait, you didn't
get a spot here?

12:20.391 --> 12:22.829
- Spokane.
Washington.

12:22.872 --> 12:26.397
- Wow.
That's incredible.

12:27.659 --> 12:29.183
- It is, isn't it?

12:29.226 --> 12:31.359
I haven't even told my mom yet.

12:31.402 --> 12:33.187
- Well, what are you
waiting for?

12:33.230 --> 12:36.277
Give her a call.
Let her be a proud mama.

12:36.320 --> 12:38.061
- She's gonna explode.

12:40.063 --> 12:42.979
<i>[solemn music]</i>

12:43.023 --> 12:49.681
<i>♪</i>

12:50.421 --> 12:51.727
- So, you just chose
to ignore

12:51.771 --> 12:54.599
my residency recommendation
for Leyla Shinwari.

12:54.643 --> 12:56.558
- [sighs]

12:56.601 --> 12:58.995
I have been on the phone
all morning with board members

12:59.039 --> 13:01.302
and angry doctors
just like yourself,

13:01.345 --> 13:03.608
all astonished
that their personal recs

13:03.652 --> 13:05.828
didn't open the doors
for their hand-picked proteges.

13:05.872 --> 13:08.875
- No, Dr. Shinwari is one of
the most promising candidates

13:08.918 --> 13:11.573
we've had in years, okay?
She deserves to be here.

13:11.616 --> 13:13.444
- Yet her application
says otherwise.

13:13.488 --> 13:14.750
Khyber Medical University?

13:14.794 --> 13:16.839
- One of the best
medical schools in Pakistan.

13:16.883 --> 13:18.667
- That has no
international standing.

13:18.710 --> 13:22.410
- She practiced medicine
in refugee camps, Hank.

13:22.453 --> 13:24.151
Okay?
The fact that she even

13:24.194 --> 13:27.241
has to redo her residency
is offensive.

13:27.284 --> 13:28.851
- Well, even if I agree
with you, what can I do?

13:28.895 --> 13:31.767
I--I can't rescind an offer
that's already been made.

13:31.811 --> 13:33.769
I can't make another spot
just magically appear.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.815
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Well, what about two years ago?

13:35.858 --> 13:37.425
Huh?
[stammers]

13:37.468 --> 13:40.776
A fifth spot just magically
opened up in general surgery.

13:40.820 --> 13:41.995
- It was hardly magic.

13:42.038 --> 13:43.866
- Well then,
what the hell was it, Hank?

13:45.650 --> 13:47.870
- You want Dr. Shinwari
on your ED?

13:47.914 --> 13:49.785
You want a fifth spot?

13:51.656 --> 13:53.180
The dean of medicine
has been known

13:53.223 --> 13:58.141
to make allowances
for the right price.

13:58.185 --> 13:59.447
- Are you talking
about a bribe?

13:59.490 --> 14:01.536
- What do you want me to say?

14:01.579 --> 14:03.799
- That is a federal crime,
Hank.

14:03.843 --> 14:05.279
I could lose
my medical license.

14:05.322 --> 14:06.671
I could go to jail.

14:06.715 --> 14:07.890
- I'm just telling you
what I've heard.

14:07.934 --> 14:09.065
Not suggesting you do it.

14:09.109 --> 14:11.415
- Of course,
I am not gonna do it.

14:17.987 --> 14:21.164
[sobbing]

14:23.166 --> 14:26.300
[screaming]

14:28.868 --> 14:31.871
[sobbing]

14:41.706 --> 14:48.626
<i>♪</i>

14:49.889 --> 14:51.325
Dear God...

14:53.501 --> 14:55.416
<i>Grant me the serenity</i>

14:55.459 --> 14:58.985
<i>to accept the things
I cannot change,</i>

14:59.028 --> 15:02.640
<i>the courage
to change the things I can.</i>

15:03.946 --> 15:05.513
Dear God,

15:05.556 --> 15:07.428
grant me the serenity

15:07.471 --> 15:10.822
to accept the things
I cannot change,

15:10.866 --> 15:13.477
the courage
to change the things I can...

15:15.871 --> 15:18.482
And the wisdom
to know the difference.

15:38.763 --> 15:40.374
- This is just...

15:40.417 --> 15:43.159
[drink pouring]

15:43.203 --> 15:45.901
Thank you.

15:45.945 --> 15:48.860
<i>[gentle piano music]</i>

15:48.904 --> 15:51.341
- Congratulations.

15:53.430 --> 15:57.608
- Look, I have been
feeling guilty all day.

15:57.652 --> 15:59.349
- Why?

15:59.393 --> 16:00.960
- I was just so excited.

16:01.003 --> 16:03.266
I didn't even think about what
you must have been feeling.

16:03.310 --> 16:07.749
And I want you to know that I'm
not excited to be leaving you.

16:07.792 --> 16:09.925
You're everything to me.
- Leyla.

16:09.969 --> 16:12.188
- I can make this work.

16:12.232 --> 16:14.190
I can.

16:14.234 --> 16:17.411
I don't have a choice.

16:17.454 --> 16:19.326
I'm in love with you.

16:21.545 --> 16:24.679
[phone ringing]

16:25.941 --> 16:28.204
- No, you should--
you should get that.

16:28.248 --> 16:31.773
- Are you sure?
- Yeah. Yeah.

16:31.816 --> 16:33.818
- Hello?

16:33.862 --> 16:36.343
Yes, this is she.

16:36.386 --> 16:40.390
Okay. Okay.

16:40.434 --> 16:42.958
[inhales]
Are you serious?

16:43.002 --> 16:45.091
That's--

16:45.134 --> 16:46.614
I don't know what to say.

16:46.657 --> 16:50.313
Yes! Yes. Thank you.

16:53.142 --> 16:55.971
That was the residency director
from New Amsterdam.

16:56.015 --> 17:00.062
The dean just opened up
a fifth spot in the ED.

17:00.106 --> 17:01.890
And they offered it to me.

17:03.674 --> 17:07.809
- That's amazing!
Congratulations!

17:07.852 --> 17:10.768
- Did you have anything
to do with this?

17:10.811 --> 17:14.294
- What? No.
No, of course not.

17:14.337 --> 17:16.339
No, this--this was all you.

17:16.383 --> 17:18.515
Oh.

17:21.474 --> 17:23.694
It was all you.

17:29.439 --> 17:31.572
- I moved across Lenox,
not the country.

17:31.615 --> 17:33.661
I'll still see you
all the time, Mama.

17:33.704 --> 17:35.750
Okay, yeah, just--

17:35.793 --> 17:38.666
try to remember I'm not
a little boy anymore, okay?

17:38.709 --> 17:41.625
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

17:41.669 --> 17:44.454
<i>♪</i>

17:44.498 --> 17:46.108
House special.

17:46.152 --> 17:48.676
- Oh, what?
- Bam.

17:50.591 --> 17:53.594
- Oh, my gosh.

17:53.637 --> 17:54.986
Mmm.

17:59.339 --> 18:00.688
If I didn't know any better,

18:00.731 --> 18:02.603
I'd say you're trying
to get me to move in.

18:02.646 --> 18:04.518
- Would that be so bad?

18:04.561 --> 18:11.481
<i>♪</i>

18:15.311 --> 18:17.139
- Mm, all right. Okay. Okay.

18:17.183 --> 18:20.142
- What?
- You know the rules.

18:20.186 --> 18:22.449
- I also know that rules
are meant to be broken.

18:22.492 --> 18:24.842
- And we have.

18:24.886 --> 18:26.366
You get one stay.

18:26.409 --> 18:29.282
Somewhere along the line,
this turned into Thursday.

18:29.325 --> 18:32.198
- Okay.
Look, look, I get it.

18:32.241 --> 18:35.288
I tried to resist you
for months, right?

18:35.331 --> 18:38.465
Finally had to give in.
Now look who can't resist.

18:38.508 --> 18:41.163
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- [chuckles]

18:41.207 --> 18:43.296
- Of course I'd fall
for two alpha males.

18:43.339 --> 18:44.949
- Oh, okay, hold on.

18:44.993 --> 18:46.995
No, I got a rule, too,
all right?

18:47.038 --> 18:49.519
None of that husband talk.

18:49.563 --> 18:51.130
Come here.

18:51.173 --> 18:53.088
- Floyd.
- Yeah.

18:54.437 --> 18:56.657
- This is the arrangement.

18:56.700 --> 19:00.313
We can never be more than this.
Tell me you know that.

19:03.229 --> 19:05.144
- Yeah, I know.

19:08.147 --> 19:10.105
- I am going to take a shower.

19:10.149 --> 19:17.243
<i>♪</i>

19:21.116 --> 19:23.684
- Dextrocardia doesn't explain
the excessive bleeding.

19:23.727 --> 19:26.513
- Not just her heart, but all
of her organs are flipped.

19:26.556 --> 19:28.863
- Then her spleen
is on the right side.

19:28.906 --> 19:31.082
- Which means the dagger is
plunging straight through it.

19:31.126 --> 19:32.562
- But that doesn't
explain the LOC.

19:32.606 --> 19:34.477
- Stop for a head CT
on your way to the OR.

19:34.521 --> 19:36.523
- Good idea.
All right.

19:36.566 --> 19:38.307
I'll need the largest OR
that's empty

19:38.351 --> 19:40.004
and every unit of O-neg we got.

19:40.048 --> 19:41.528
- Already ordered
and waiting for you.

19:41.571 --> 19:43.225
- Okay, good.
We'll also need a fresh staff

19:43.269 --> 19:44.357
that can work
at least 12 hours.

19:44.400 --> 19:45.880
This one's gonna be a marathon.

19:45.923 --> 19:47.229
- I'll round them up.
- I've got a full craniotomy

19:47.273 --> 19:48.491
set up on order for you.
- Oh!

19:48.535 --> 19:50.363
Perfect timing.
I'll take her from here.

19:50.406 --> 19:51.842
- Wait. What?
- Dr. Salaita.

19:51.886 --> 19:54.802
The CT showed Ms. Madera
threw a clot from her abdomen

19:54.845 --> 19:56.760
up through her poorly-formed
heart to her brain,

19:56.804 --> 19:58.371
where it caused
a hemorrhagic event.

19:58.414 --> 19:59.502
You'll need to drain the blood
from her head.

19:59.546 --> 20:01.025
- Our team's waiting,
Dr. Baptiste.

20:01.069 --> 20:02.418
- Okay, get a scanner in here

20:02.462 --> 20:03.811
so you can do a real-time,
image-guided surgery.

20:03.854 --> 20:05.552
- They'll never let me have
the IGS system, sir.

20:05.595 --> 20:06.814
- Tell them
the chief of surgery

20:06.857 --> 20:08.076
personally authorized it.

20:08.119 --> 20:09.382
Dr. Flores, gather your team

20:09.425 --> 20:10.731
for the septal reconstruction.

20:10.774 --> 20:12.341
You'll be last,
so just wait in the obs deck.

20:12.385 --> 20:14.387
- Will do, sir.
- And you.

20:14.430 --> 20:15.866
You're the associate
ED trauma surgeon?

20:15.910 --> 20:18.739
- Dr. Reynolds. Yes, sir.
- Let's see what you've got.

20:21.872 --> 20:24.919
- All right, here we go.
Get the lap pads ready.

20:24.962 --> 20:30.533
<i>♪</i>

20:30.577 --> 20:32.840
Dagger's out.
- Replaced by blood.

20:32.883 --> 20:34.668
There's gotta be a bleeder
in here somewhere.

20:34.711 --> 20:36.365
- Whew.
- Another lap pad.

20:36.409 --> 20:38.367
- Still can't see it.

20:41.065 --> 20:42.937
Come on.

20:42.980 --> 20:44.460
Come on. Come on.

20:46.723 --> 20:49.465
Got it. Suture.

20:50.466 --> 20:52.033
- Monitor the systolic pulse...

20:52.076 --> 20:53.556
- With situs inversus,

20:53.600 --> 20:56.603
we got small mini-spleens
all through her abdomen.

20:56.646 --> 20:58.474
Once I get this under control,
I can remove them.

20:58.518 --> 21:00.955
- No need; I'll do it myself
during the brain surgery.

21:00.998 --> 21:03.218
Did you get a CT angio to
locate the accessory spleens?

21:03.262 --> 21:05.960
- Scissors. I did not.

21:06.003 --> 21:09.311
You know what they say:
death begins in radiology.

21:09.355 --> 21:11.182
- [indistinct] standing by.

21:12.836 --> 21:15.143
- That should hold.

21:15.186 --> 21:16.449
- I can assist
in the splenectomy.

21:16.492 --> 21:18.320
- You're dismissed.

21:18.364 --> 21:20.235
Where's my neuro team?
You guys are up.

21:20.279 --> 21:21.323
- Make sure
there's enough blood...

21:21.367 --> 21:23.934
- Switch up.

21:23.978 --> 21:26.328
<i>[percussive music]</i>

21:26.372 --> 21:31.333
<i>♪</i>

21:47.523 --> 21:50.439
- Do you dry clean?

21:50.483 --> 21:52.354
Got a couple of shirts
that could use a press.

21:52.398 --> 21:54.400
- Lost my wedding ring.
- Oof.

21:54.443 --> 21:56.750
Well, you didn't have it
on this morning, if that helps.

21:56.793 --> 21:59.100
- You notice who's
wearing a wedding ring?

21:59.143 --> 22:00.362
- Recently.

22:00.406 --> 22:03.017
- I have looked
everywhere for it.

22:03.060 --> 22:05.106
I'm gonna be sifting through
medical waste pretty soon.

22:05.149 --> 22:07.717
- I guess I just assumed
you took it off on purpose.

22:07.761 --> 22:10.024
- No.

22:10.067 --> 22:11.852
[sighs]

22:11.895 --> 22:14.376
I don't know.

22:14.420 --> 22:17.684
Still means something, I guess.

22:17.727 --> 22:19.381
I mean, it's everything we had,
you know?

22:19.425 --> 22:22.863
It's like--come on,
it can't just be gone.

22:22.906 --> 22:27.215
- Actually, uh, I felt
the same way about Evie's ring

22:27.258 --> 22:30.784
after we, uh, you know.

22:30.827 --> 22:32.263
- So what changed?

22:32.307 --> 22:34.875
- Well, I realized I wasn't
hanging on to Evie's ring

22:34.918 --> 22:39.401
because she still had
a big piece of my heart.

22:39.445 --> 22:42.839
I was hanging on to it
because she didn't.

22:42.883 --> 22:45.407
And the ring wasn't
about our love anymore.

22:46.930 --> 22:48.584
It was about my guilt.

22:51.108 --> 22:53.763
- Dr. Reynolds, Dr. Flores
needs you in the OR, stat.

23:00.944 --> 23:02.424
- Flores?
- I'm trying to pull off

23:02.468 --> 23:03.904
a triangular patch
reconstruction

23:03.947 --> 23:05.949
of the ventricular wall.
You've done one?

23:05.993 --> 23:07.560
- Several times.
- I just can't get it to hold.

23:07.603 --> 23:09.866
- All right. I got it.
- BP's still dropping.

23:09.910 --> 23:11.564
- We need to increase
patch adhesion

23:11.607 --> 23:13.696
to seal
microcirculatory leakage.

23:13.740 --> 23:15.698
Go ahead and clamp
the inferior vena cava.

23:15.742 --> 23:17.700
I'm gonna apply
direct pressure.

23:17.744 --> 23:19.354
On my signal,
I want you to squeeze

23:19.398 --> 23:20.660
the largest piece
of spleen you can fine.

23:20.703 --> 23:22.879
- Mm-hmm.
- All right?

23:22.923 --> 23:24.707
Ready. Now.

23:24.751 --> 23:27.188
Okay.

23:27.231 --> 23:31.192
All right, so go ahead and
slowly release the vena cava.

23:31.235 --> 23:34.456
All right.
Now increase the flow.

23:34.500 --> 23:37.938
Gently. Ah. Slow it down.

23:37.981 --> 23:41.855
Okay. And all the way.

23:41.898 --> 23:45.554
[machine beeping]

23:46.642 --> 23:48.818
[indistinct chatter]

23:50.951 --> 23:54.302
- I don't see any leaking.
- Nice save, Floyd.

23:54.345 --> 23:55.825
We'll close her up.

23:58.175 --> 24:00.613
- Dr. Reynolds.

24:00.656 --> 24:03.311
After surgery,
may I have a word?

24:03.354 --> 24:05.922
- Get another blanket
on her leg.

24:06.662 --> 24:10.100
<i>- Custodial services, 224.
Custodial services, 224.</i>

24:12.276 --> 24:15.628
- I've only been here
a little while, so tell me.

24:15.671 --> 24:17.238
How'd you end up buried deep
in the ED--

24:17.281 --> 24:19.370
please, please, have a seat--

24:19.414 --> 24:21.372
associate trauma surgeon?

24:22.548 --> 24:25.464
- It's the only spot
I could get.

24:25.507 --> 24:26.943
- You never mentioned
you used to be

24:26.987 --> 24:30.338
the chair
of cardiothoracic surgery?

24:30.381 --> 24:31.905
So what happened?

24:31.948 --> 24:33.907
- Well,
I left about a year ago.

24:33.950 --> 24:35.125
- Poached?

24:35.169 --> 24:36.997
- Engaged.
[chuckles]

24:37.040 --> 24:40.348
Yeah, my fiancée got
her dream job in San Francisco,

24:40.391 --> 24:42.219
so I followed.

24:42.263 --> 24:44.221
Long story short, I'm back.

24:44.265 --> 24:46.006
- We got a lot in common.

24:46.049 --> 24:48.399
I followed my girl
out here too.

24:48.443 --> 24:52.621
But one big difference: my job
makes full use of my talents.

24:52.665 --> 24:56.016
Yours doesn't.
- Well, I'm not complaining.

24:56.059 --> 24:57.496
- And I'm not insulting.

24:57.539 --> 25:00.542
I'm offering you a promotion.
Deputy chair of surgery.

25:00.586 --> 25:03.502
<i>[hopeful music]</i>

25:03.545 --> 25:04.981
<i>♪</i>

25:05.025 --> 25:06.548
- That's a big promotion.

25:06.592 --> 25:07.680
- Bigger than
chair of cardiothoracic.

25:07.723 --> 25:11.031
- To say the least.

25:11.074 --> 25:13.816
- Is that a yes?
- Oh, yes, it is. Thank you.

25:13.860 --> 25:16.253
I--I don't know what to say,
but thank you.

25:16.297 --> 25:17.428
- You're welcome.
You're welcome.

25:17.472 --> 25:18.517
[knock at door]
- Knock, knock.

25:18.560 --> 25:20.344
- Hey, sweetheart.

25:20.388 --> 25:21.563
- Hey.

25:25.698 --> 25:27.003
- Dr. Reynolds, Dr. Lyn Malvo,

25:27.047 --> 25:29.179
my wife, the one who lured me
to New Amsterdam.

25:29.223 --> 25:31.573
- [laughs]

25:31.617 --> 25:33.183
Nice to meet you.

25:33.227 --> 25:36.143
- Floyd's gonna be
my new right-hand man.

25:36.186 --> 25:39.581
- Wow. Congratulations.

25:39.625 --> 25:43.063
<i>[percussive music]</i>

25:43.106 --> 25:44.891
- [chuckles]

25:49.591 --> 25:52.159
<i>[serene music]</i>

25:52.202 --> 25:56.250
<i>♪</i>

25:56.293 --> 25:58.121
all: ♪ 37 bottles of juice
on the wall ♪

25:58.165 --> 26:00.471
♪ 37 bottles of juice

26:00.515 --> 26:03.300
♪ You take one down,
pass it around ♪

26:03.344 --> 26:05.868
♪ 36 bottles
of juice on the wall ♪

26:05.912 --> 26:07.740
♪ 36 bottles of juice

26:07.783 --> 26:10.351
♪ You take one down,
pass it around ♪

26:10.394 --> 26:12.701
♪ 35 bottles
of juice on the wall ♪

26:12.745 --> 26:14.268
- Air guitar version!

26:14.311 --> 26:16.313
all: ♪ 35 bottles of juice
on the wall ♪

26:16.357 --> 26:18.489
♪ 35 bottles of juice

26:18.533 --> 26:20.666
♪ Take one down,
pass it around ♪

26:20.709 --> 26:22.798
♪ 34 bottles of juice
on the wall ♪

26:22.842 --> 26:25.148
- And cut. Papa needs a break.

26:25.192 --> 26:27.324
- No, guys, let's sing
some harmonies, come on.

26:27.368 --> 26:29.631
- Or we can enjoy
the meditative silence

26:29.675 --> 26:32.678
of a solid 45 minutes
of screen time.

26:32.721 --> 26:35.506
kids: Yes!

26:35.550 --> 26:37.552
- Boo. Boo.

26:37.596 --> 26:44.515
<i>♪</i>

26:48.041 --> 26:49.912
- All right,
dinner is in one hour.

26:49.956 --> 26:51.218
Tell your brothers and sister.

26:51.261 --> 26:52.523
- Okay, when I'm done.
- Oh, "When I'm done."

26:52.567 --> 26:53.524
When she's done.

26:53.568 --> 26:55.135
- She sassing you?
- Yeah.

26:55.178 --> 26:57.137
- Gosh.

26:57.180 --> 26:59.443
You know, I hate to say it,
but I think, um,

26:59.487 --> 27:01.010
I think we've been
COVID-blessed out here, babe.

27:01.054 --> 27:02.621
- Yeah.
- You know, look at us.

27:02.664 --> 27:04.274
We're out here being a family,
camping, making slingshots,

27:04.318 --> 27:05.536
she's giving you sass.

27:05.580 --> 27:07.147
- [laughs]
- I love it.

27:07.190 --> 27:08.365
Kind of begs the question,

27:08.409 --> 27:09.845
why don't we just
stay here indefinitely?

27:09.889 --> 27:11.630
- Uh, Iggy.

27:11.673 --> 27:12.718
- I'm just having
a little fantasy.

27:12.761 --> 27:13.936
Let me have my fantasy.
- All right.

27:13.980 --> 27:15.024
Look, the kids are going back

27:15.068 --> 27:17.244
to in-person learning
full-time.

27:17.287 --> 27:19.159
I need to get back
to my practice,

27:19.202 --> 27:22.162
and you need to get back
to the hospital.

27:22.205 --> 27:24.468
- Yeah, well, what if
I'm not ready to go back?

27:24.512 --> 27:26.688
- So, uh, we're gonna live out
of a rented RV

27:26.732 --> 27:28.734
in upstate New York?
- Pfft, no.

27:28.777 --> 27:30.170
I thought maybe we'd live
out of a rented RV

27:30.213 --> 27:32.999
in upstate Vermont next.

27:33.042 --> 27:35.566
[laughs]

27:35.610 --> 27:37.090
What?

27:37.133 --> 27:38.831
- You can't just
keep running, Iggs.

27:38.874 --> 27:40.833
- I'm not.

27:43.052 --> 27:44.750
I'm not.

27:44.793 --> 27:49.102
- Help! Help!

27:49.145 --> 27:51.060
Ah!

27:51.104 --> 27:52.540
kids:
Dad!

27:52.583 --> 27:53.584
- What happened?

27:53.628 --> 27:55.717
- Come on. Come on.
- Dad! Dad!

27:55.761 --> 27:57.284
- Please!
- Father!

27:57.327 --> 27:58.851
- Ow.
- Slow down. Slow down.

27:58.894 --> 28:00.417
- Splinter.

28:00.461 --> 28:02.637
- Show us.
- Oh. Oh. Whoa.

28:02.681 --> 28:05.553
Mamacita, you took
some shrapnel there, buddy.

28:05.596 --> 28:07.686
Okay, but fortunately for you,
our crack team

28:07.729 --> 28:09.600
of surgeons are at the ready.
- Yeah.

28:09.644 --> 28:12.516
- Harper, bring me
the instruments of abscission.

28:12.560 --> 28:13.866
- What?
- That old rusty saw

28:13.909 --> 28:14.954
we found by the dumpster.

28:14.997 --> 28:16.259
You know what they are.
- Dad!

28:16.303 --> 28:17.957
- Saleem, bring me a towel
for all the blood

28:18.000 --> 28:19.741
and a bucket to put
the severed limb in, stat.

28:19.785 --> 28:21.830
- You got it.
- Dad, be serious.

28:21.874 --> 28:24.746
- I--kid, I am being serious.
This is war, all right?

28:24.790 --> 28:26.313
- Here you go.

28:26.356 --> 28:28.097
- I promise you it'll be over
in a couple seconds, okay?

28:28.141 --> 28:29.751
Harper, look away.

28:29.795 --> 28:32.275
Nobody move. Nobody breathe.
Except for me.

28:32.319 --> 28:35.017
I have to breathe, obviously.
I'm the doctor.

28:35.061 --> 28:36.976
Here we go. Almost there.

28:37.019 --> 28:38.368
Yes.
- Oh!

28:38.412 --> 28:40.153
- Victory.
- Look at that beast.

28:40.196 --> 28:41.676
- Whoa.

28:41.720 --> 28:43.199
- Look at that thing.
That was inside your finger.

28:43.243 --> 28:44.461
- Disgusting.
- I'll say.

28:44.505 --> 28:45.767
- That is a serious
piece of timber.

28:45.811 --> 28:47.421
- Actually, don't throw
that away.

28:47.464 --> 28:48.683
We might want to ride that
down the Susquehanna later.

28:48.727 --> 28:49.902
- [laughs]
- We're a big family.

28:49.945 --> 28:51.468
- Probably sink with all of us.

28:51.512 --> 28:53.427
- Oh yeah, right.
Not with me as a captain.

28:53.470 --> 28:55.908
- We have five family members.
- You are brave, private.

28:55.951 --> 28:57.431
Sameera?

28:57.474 --> 29:00.303
I need you
to bandage this soldier.

29:00.347 --> 29:02.175
- Sameera.
- Sameera.

29:02.218 --> 29:03.567
- What, did she go back
to the car?

29:03.611 --> 29:06.048
- Uh, I don't know.
Did you guys see Sameera?

29:06.092 --> 29:07.528
- Sameera.

29:07.571 --> 29:08.877
- She was just here.
She couldn't have gone far.

29:08.921 --> 29:10.313
- Sameera!
- Sameera!

29:10.357 --> 29:12.054
- Sameera.

29:12.098 --> 29:13.490
- All right, um, you take

29:13.534 --> 29:14.665
everybody back to the RV.
- Hon.

29:14.709 --> 29:16.145
- No, no, I'm gonna
go look for her.

29:16.189 --> 29:17.756
You find out where the nearest
ranger station is, okay?

29:17.799 --> 29:19.496
- Guys, guys, stay close.
Stay close.

29:19.540 --> 29:22.108
- Sameera.
- Sameera!

29:22.151 --> 29:23.979
- Sammy!

29:24.023 --> 29:27.417
<i>[tense music]</i>

29:27.461 --> 29:30.333
Sameera!
Sameera?

29:30.377 --> 29:31.900
Sameera, baby!

29:34.250 --> 29:36.513
Sameera!

29:40.039 --> 29:41.344
Oh, God.

29:41.388 --> 29:42.824
Oh, God, no.

29:42.868 --> 29:49.613
<i>♪</i>

29:53.574 --> 29:56.011
Sameera!

29:56.055 --> 29:57.970
Sameera?
Sameera, honey.

29:58.013 --> 29:59.754
I'm coming.

29:59.798 --> 30:03.236
[grunting]

30:09.372 --> 30:10.809
Sameera, honey?

30:12.462 --> 30:15.248
Sameera, if you can hear me,
answer me, baby.

30:16.249 --> 30:19.295
Sameera!
[stick thunking]

30:19.339 --> 30:20.906
Sameera.

30:28.217 --> 30:30.350
Sameera!

30:30.393 --> 30:31.786
Sameera.
Oh, my God.

30:31.830 --> 30:33.832
Did you--baby, did you not
hear me calling you?

30:33.875 --> 30:37.400
Why didn't you answer me?
Sameera, honey, say something.

30:40.099 --> 30:41.448
- I don't want to go back.

30:41.491 --> 30:42.710
- You don't want--you don't
wanna go back where?

30:42.753 --> 30:44.581
You don't want to go back
to the campsite?

30:44.625 --> 30:47.454
You don't wanna--
- Back to normal.

30:47.497 --> 30:49.891
- Back to normal?

30:49.935 --> 30:52.589
What is it?
Is it school? Are you--

30:52.633 --> 30:54.374
- I like school better
on the computer.

30:54.417 --> 30:56.332
I learn better.

30:56.376 --> 30:58.508
- Yeah.

30:58.552 --> 31:00.423
Yeah, but what about
your friends, baby?

31:00.467 --> 31:01.772
What about all them?

31:01.816 --> 31:04.775
- I'd rather be here
with you and Papa,

31:04.819 --> 31:08.301
eating lunch together,
playing together.

31:08.344 --> 31:10.303
Everything's easier at home.

31:10.346 --> 31:12.261
<i>[sentimental music]</i>

31:12.305 --> 31:13.915
- Yeah.

31:13.959 --> 31:15.612
<i>[gentle acoustic music]</i>

31:15.656 --> 31:18.528
Yeah. I like it too.

31:18.572 --> 31:21.444
- So why do we have
to go back?

31:21.488 --> 31:23.838
- Well, because...

31:23.882 --> 31:28.190
<i>♪</i>

31:28.234 --> 31:30.540
Because it's not
supposed to be easy.

31:32.107 --> 31:35.806
You know, asking your teacher
for help over and over again,

31:35.850 --> 31:39.680
that helps you become
more resilient.

31:39.723 --> 31:41.029
Navigating tricky friendships,

31:41.073 --> 31:42.857
even though it's a pain
in your butt,

31:42.901 --> 31:46.165
that builds self-esteem,
you know?

31:46.208 --> 31:49.951
<i>♪</i>

31:49.995 --> 31:53.172
Life is starting again.

31:53.215 --> 31:57.306
We can't stay here

31:57.350 --> 31:59.787
where it's easy.

32:02.442 --> 32:04.748
Make sense, kiddo?

32:09.971 --> 32:10.972
[indistinct chatter]

32:11.016 --> 32:14.802
- Well, that was
quite the adventure.

32:15.672 --> 32:18.414
- Oh, my God, that one...
- It's roasted.

32:18.458 --> 32:20.025
- You okay?
- Oh, my God.

32:20.068 --> 32:21.722
- Yeah, yeah.

32:21.765 --> 32:24.986
You know,
when Sameera went missing,

32:25.030 --> 32:27.989
I just had
these visions of Chance.

32:28.033 --> 32:29.251
Hurting her.

32:29.295 --> 32:30.687
- Iggy--
- I know. I know.

32:30.731 --> 32:33.386
I know it's irrational.
I know that in my heart.

32:35.736 --> 32:38.434
There he was, you know,
clear as day.

32:38.478 --> 32:40.175
- [blowing]
Yes! It's golden.

32:40.219 --> 32:41.872
- And why not?

32:41.916 --> 32:46.355
You know, day after day,
I just absorbed his despair.

32:46.399 --> 32:48.444
It all just became
a part of me.

32:48.488 --> 32:50.011
All my patients,
all their despair,

32:50.055 --> 32:53.972
it just--it just becomes
a part of me.

32:56.409 --> 32:57.671
But it was all worth it,
you know,

32:57.714 --> 32:59.325
because at the end of the day,
I can just trade

32:59.368 --> 33:02.632
my peace of mind for
the self-esteem it brought me.

33:02.676 --> 33:04.069
Easy-peasy.
[chuckles]

33:06.636 --> 33:09.335
I don't wanna
make that trade anymore.

33:09.378 --> 33:12.773
I don't--I don't need to.

33:12.816 --> 33:16.429
Look at this.
Look at what we've done.

33:16.472 --> 33:19.562
[kids laughing, chattering]

33:20.824 --> 33:23.653
Martin, you give me
everything that I need.

33:26.569 --> 33:30.486
Our family gives me...

33:33.185 --> 33:35.230
Everything.

33:35.274 --> 33:42.455
<i>♪</i>

33:44.631 --> 33:48.417
We can go home
whenever you need to.

33:48.461 --> 33:50.767
No more running. I promise.

33:57.861 --> 34:00.995
But I am not going
to see patients anymore.

34:03.432 --> 34:05.869
I'm done with that life.

34:07.480 --> 34:11.266
[kids laughing]

34:11.310 --> 34:13.181
- Watch it--I got mine on fire.

34:15.313 --> 34:17.098
- [sighs]

34:20.884 --> 34:23.844
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

34:23.887 --> 34:26.455
<i>♪</i>

34:26.498 --> 34:28.065
- [scoffs]

34:30.024 --> 34:31.112
I knew you hated
budget meetings,

34:31.156 --> 34:33.679
but this seems extreme.

34:33.723 --> 34:35.551
- I lost my wedding ring.

34:40.165 --> 34:42.384
- Max. Come out from there.
- [sighs]

34:42.428 --> 34:44.386
I can't do it.
- Come on.

34:44.429 --> 34:45.953
- Mm-mm.

34:45.996 --> 34:47.520
- [sighs]

34:49.783 --> 34:51.306
I mean, rings do hold

34:51.350 --> 34:55.136
a certain amount
of symbolic power over us.

34:55.179 --> 34:57.573
Don't they?
- Yeah.

34:57.617 --> 34:59.401
- I should know.
I've had three.

34:59.445 --> 35:02.143
- Three. You get it.

35:02.187 --> 35:05.015
- Oh, Max, I get it.

35:05.059 --> 35:06.278
You feel like you're losing
a limb.

35:06.321 --> 35:07.975
Part of your life.

35:08.018 --> 35:09.672
And if it can be lost
that easily,

35:09.716 --> 35:11.065
then what does that say?

35:11.109 --> 35:14.721
- Says you didn't deserve it.

35:14.764 --> 35:16.940
- All right,
come out of there now.

35:16.984 --> 35:18.159
Come on.
- Do I have to?

35:18.203 --> 35:20.161
- Yes.
- [groans]

35:20.205 --> 35:23.121
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

35:23.164 --> 35:25.253
<i>♪</i>

35:25.297 --> 35:27.777
If I've learned anything...

35:30.302 --> 35:33.043
It's knowing
when to let them go.

35:33.087 --> 35:34.436
When to move on.

35:34.480 --> 35:37.091
- I want to move on. I do.

35:37.135 --> 35:39.224
But I didn't get
to make that decision.

35:39.267 --> 35:42.531
That choice was taken from me.

35:43.837 --> 35:46.318
- She'd understand.

35:49.103 --> 35:50.539
Max.

35:52.062 --> 35:53.412
Look at me.

35:56.763 --> 35:59.722
She'd understand.

35:59.766 --> 36:01.289
- I almost took it off.

36:02.551 --> 36:04.684
On the anniversary of her--

36:07.643 --> 36:09.297
- Why didn't you?

36:11.473 --> 36:14.302
- Because when I look at Luna,

36:14.346 --> 36:16.739
I don't even
see Georgia anymore.

36:18.132 --> 36:20.917
I just see my little girl.

36:20.961 --> 36:25.444
And when I look inside,
Georgia's not there either.

36:27.054 --> 36:30.231
That ring--

36:30.275 --> 36:33.234
it's all I have left...

36:33.278 --> 36:34.714
[chuckles]

36:34.757 --> 36:37.151
Of our whole life.

36:38.544 --> 36:42.983
- Well, it didn't just
slip off your finger.

36:43.026 --> 36:45.420
There's a reason
you took it off.

36:45.464 --> 36:47.857
Maybe you should trust
your subconscious.

36:47.901 --> 36:51.600
- Yeah.
Yeah.

36:51.644 --> 36:53.820
Like I'm trying
to tell myself something.

36:53.863 --> 36:57.215
- Found it.
- What? Really? Wow! Yes!

36:57.258 --> 36:59.434
You're amazing. Thank you.
I gotta go.

36:59.478 --> 37:01.784
Sorry. Wow. I--thank you.

37:01.828 --> 37:03.308
Thank you,
Sandra Fall from billing.

37:03.351 --> 37:04.744
